WEBVTT

00:02.700 --> 00:03.367
Previously on "Below Deck"...

00:03.367 --> 00:03.667
Previously on "Below Deck"...
- You don't like it?

00:05.400 --> 00:07.133
If it were my restaurant,

00:07.133 --> 00:09.000
a lot of things
would have been sent back.

00:09.000 --> 00:10.367
- I'm a little concerned
with what I saw in the galley.

00:10.367 --> 00:12.233
I need Matt to stand
on his own two feet.

00:12.233 --> 00:13.700
I'd like to see you
really pull out all the stops.

00:13.700 --> 00:15.367
- I'm so burnt out.

00:15.367 --> 00:16.500
I've had criticism
up the yin-yang.

00:16.500 --> 00:18.033
I'm done.

00:18.033 --> 00:19.667
- When the charter ends,
I'm out of here.

00:19.667 --> 00:21.533
- I'm gonna miss you so much.

00:21.533 --> 00:23.100
Bye.

00:23.100 --> 00:25.000
- We're gonna have
a new deckhand, so...

00:25.000 --> 00:26.533
- Look who it is.
- What's up?

00:28.133 --> 00:30.100
- Hi.
- Shelly Snoddy.

00:30.100 --> 00:31.300
She wants her girlfriends
to get together

00:31.300 --> 00:32.500
and have a good time.

00:32.500 --> 00:34.033
- Nico, watch this.

00:34.033 --> 00:35.667
- I like you, Jen.

00:35.667 --> 00:36.767
I can win an argument
with you quite quickly.

00:36.767 --> 00:38.300
We should get married.

00:38.300 --> 00:39.333
- Oh, my God,
we're holding hands.

00:39.333 --> 00:41.000
It's so official.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.300
I like him.
I like him a lot.

00:42.300 --> 00:43.300
I'm excited to spend time
with him.

00:49.066 --> 00:50.600
- You seem miserable.

00:50.600 --> 00:52.734
- No, you seem
very out of line right now.

00:52.734 --> 00:55.033
- This is a friend of a friend.
- You're not my friend.

00:55.033 --> 00:57.200
- Kate's pushed me
to my boiling point.

00:57.200 --> 00:59.000
It is what it is.

00:59.000 --> 01:00.600
- You should never call
your boss "miserable."

01:02.467 --> 01:03.567
[horn blares]

01:03.567 --> 01:06.567
[upbeat music]

01:06.567 --> 01:13.567
♪ ♪

01:22.467 --> 01:24.567
- Do you feel those
big waves down there?

01:24.567 --> 01:26.500
- Yeah.

01:26.500 --> 01:28.500
- The motion of the ocean
makes me so sleepy.

01:28.500 --> 01:29.767
I'm like a newborn baby
right now.

01:29.767 --> 01:31.233
- I was sh---ing
in the bathroom,

01:31.233 --> 01:33.033
and I was like...
- [laughs]

01:33.033 --> 01:34.700
- Kate, Kate, Lee.
- Go, Captain.

01:34.700 --> 01:37.567
- To the bridge, please.
- Copy.

01:39.734 --> 01:41.166
Hi.
What's going on?

01:41.166 --> 01:43.734
- I had a conversation
with Chef.

01:54.767 --> 01:56.467
- Yeah.

01:56.467 --> 01:58.300
Basically, you need
to prove yourselves.

01:58.300 --> 01:59.700
- [laughs]

01:59.700 --> 02:01.100
- As long as
the next charter group

02:01.100 --> 02:03.600
doesn't have, like, super...

02:03.600 --> 02:05.333
- I think they do.
- High-end...

02:05.333 --> 02:07.066
- I'm hoping
that our conversation

02:07.066 --> 02:08.600
will get Matt
to step his game up

02:08.600 --> 02:10.367
and maybe piss him off
to the point

02:10.367 --> 02:12.133
where he goes, "I'll show
that son of a bitch."

02:12.133 --> 02:15.633
- Well, I'm glad that
we're on the same page.

02:15.633 --> 02:17.200
- What's up?
- Let's not go crazy.

02:17.200 --> 02:19.500
Let's not start talking
some sh--, okay?

02:19.500 --> 02:22.100
But I'm going in
for the kill tomorrow.

02:22.100 --> 02:23.500
- For what?

02:25.367 --> 02:27.100
- Yeah, you should.
- It's happening.

02:27.100 --> 02:28.633
You know the truth:
When I get it on, I get it on.

02:28.633 --> 02:30.333
Is it amateur hour, boys?

02:30.333 --> 02:32.133
I'm not
a particularly normal bloke,

02:32.133 --> 02:33.667
so I like the fact
a girl's a little bit crazy,

02:33.667 --> 02:35.533
'cause I can tap into that;
I can relate.

02:35.533 --> 02:36.734
- Just don't marry her, okay?

02:36.734 --> 02:38.533
- [laughs]

02:38.533 --> 02:40.734
- All right,
let's get these covers off.

02:40.734 --> 02:43.500
- [singing]

02:44.767 --> 02:47.233
- Can you squeeze the oranges?
Or did you already start?

02:47.233 --> 02:48.767
- No, I have to wait
till that brews,

02:48.767 --> 02:51.100
'cause we only have one
flippin' plug over there.

02:51.100 --> 02:52.767
- Did you try that one?

02:52.767 --> 02:54.533
- All the way at the end?
Yeah, I can do that.

02:54.533 --> 02:56.533
- It was working yesterday.
- I can try that.

02:56.533 --> 02:58.266
- I think a lot of people

02:58.266 --> 03:00.033
would have expected me
to fire Jen by now.

03:00.033 --> 03:01.233
- Wait, wait, wait.
Before you start it--

03:01.233 --> 03:03.133
- I'm not gonna start it.

03:03.133 --> 03:04.567
- Especially when you consider
the way she speaks to me.

03:04.567 --> 03:05.700
- I'm gonna go check
on the tea towels.

03:05.700 --> 03:07.400
This is f'ing annoying.

03:07.400 --> 03:09.000
- But I'm being lenient with
her

03:09.000 --> 03:10.700
because hiring
a new stewardess

03:10.700 --> 03:12.500
this late in the game
would only be more work for me.

03:14.500 --> 03:16.233
- Hey.

03:16.233 --> 03:17.300
[laughs]

03:17.300 --> 03:19.367
- Well, hello.

03:21.300 --> 03:23.100
- Doing laundry again?

03:23.100 --> 03:24.600
- No, we don't have any
dish towels up there.

03:28.433 --> 03:30.200
I actually washed deck towels,

03:30.200 --> 03:31.266
and I need to put them
in the dryer.

03:31.266 --> 03:32.734
- Jen, Jen.

03:32.734 --> 03:34.333
Could you please come
juice the oranges?

03:34.333 --> 03:35.400
The juicer works
when it's plugged in.

03:35.400 --> 03:37.200
- I had no idea.

03:37.200 --> 03:39.400
Sure, I'm on my way
with some clean dish towels.

03:39.400 --> 03:41.266
I don't give a f---

03:41.266 --> 03:42.600
if Kate's mad at me.

03:42.600 --> 03:44.433
I've been mad at her
plenty of times.

03:44.433 --> 03:46.300
I'm here, I'm working,

03:46.300 --> 03:49.066
and I'm not gonna give her
any reason to fire me.

03:49.066 --> 03:50.533
Nor will I quit.

03:50.533 --> 03:52.667
We just discussed
that it worked.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.700
Why would you reiterate that
over the radio?

03:54.700 --> 03:56.467
- Because you weren't
doing it.

03:56.467 --> 03:58.066
- I was going
to get dish towels

03:58.066 --> 03:59.467
to wipe up the juice.

03:59.467 --> 04:00.667
- Okay,
but for future reference,

04:00.667 --> 04:02.033
let's focus on charter guests.

04:02.033 --> 04:03.433
- Uh-huh, yeah.

04:03.433 --> 04:05.400
- Don't you remember
having babies

04:05.400 --> 04:07.066
and you come home
a little drunk?

04:07.066 --> 04:08.300
You'd hear that baby cry.

04:09.300 --> 04:11.066
- That was the worst:
being hungover

04:11.066 --> 04:12.600
and having to get up
with the kids.

04:18.734 --> 04:21.233
- Hey, Bri.
- Hi, hi.

04:21.233 --> 04:25.567
How are things with Kate
this morning?

04:28.066 --> 04:29.333
- She made it known?

04:29.333 --> 04:31.200
- Yeah, she attacked me.
- Oh, no.

04:31.200 --> 04:33.433
- I'm like, "Dude."

04:33.433 --> 04:35.033
- Hey.
- Hi.

04:35.033 --> 04:37.567
- Can you please go down
and do cabins?

04:37.567 --> 04:39.100
- Yes.

04:39.100 --> 04:41.233
- We'll have Bri do them.
- Okay.

04:41.233 --> 04:43.166
- You can stay up here
on service.

04:43.166 --> 04:45.500
Every day working with Jen,
I'm thankful

04:45.500 --> 04:48.400
that I'm one step closer
to not working with Jen.

04:48.400 --> 04:51.100
- Oh, the quiche,
they're really pretty.

04:51.100 --> 04:52.200
- Thanks.

04:52.200 --> 04:53.233
- On my mark,

04:53.233 --> 04:54.367
get me three shots.

04:54.367 --> 04:56.000
Drop.

04:56.000 --> 04:58.200
- Come on. Come on.
Come on.

04:58.200 --> 05:00.467
- Okay, Captain,
three in the water.

05:00.467 --> 05:02.066
- Lock it.

05:02.066 --> 05:03.367
- I need two more glasses.

05:07.066 --> 05:08.100
- Hey.

05:10.000 --> 05:11.100
- Those look good.

05:11.100 --> 05:12.600
- Quiches.
Ow.

05:12.600 --> 05:14.266
I really don't understand

05:14.266 --> 05:15.600
what problem Captain Lee has
with my cooking.

05:15.600 --> 05:17.133
The guests have seemed happy.

05:17.133 --> 05:18.133
I don't know what to tell you.

05:18.133 --> 05:19.266
We're all set.

05:19.266 --> 05:22.133
- Looks amazing.
- Thanks.

05:22.133 --> 05:23.600
- Hi, Kate.

05:23.600 --> 05:25.133
- We have your brunch set up
in the main salon,

05:25.133 --> 05:26.333
if you guys want to
go in there.

05:26.333 --> 05:28.133
- Wonderful.
- Nice.

05:28.133 --> 05:29.533
- All right, so we're going
to put out all the toys.

05:29.533 --> 05:31.166
One person on
the swim platform,

05:31.166 --> 05:32.166
and the rest of us
will go up top.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.433
Ready?
Going up.

05:34.433 --> 05:36.033
- Starboard side.

05:36.033 --> 05:37.533
I was pretty hard on EJ,

05:37.533 --> 05:39.533
but I actually do respect
the guy.

05:39.533 --> 05:42.500
He's an experienced yachty,
and I did learn a lot

05:42.500 --> 05:44.633
and really channeled in
to what I need to do

05:44.633 --> 05:46.533
and not be a dick.

05:46.533 --> 05:49.767
Actually, they're long enough.
Let's hold it from here.

05:49.767 --> 05:51.400
I want to end this season

05:51.400 --> 05:53.567
knowing I did the best
I possibly could.

05:53.567 --> 05:55.100
Okay, Bruno.

05:55.100 --> 05:56.633
- Got to get laid, Mare.
[laughter]

05:56.633 --> 05:58.367
- It's been so long.

05:58.367 --> 06:00.433
- Okay, whose turn it is
to do the quick blessing?

06:00.433 --> 06:02.166
- Bless, O Lord, these gifts
we're about to receive

06:02.166 --> 06:04.000
through Christ, O Lord, amen.

06:04.000 --> 06:06.000
- I've never said
so many prayers in my life.

06:06.000 --> 06:07.700
- No shame in Jesus.
- That's right.

06:07.700 --> 06:09.633
- Oh, this looks great.
- Better than sex.

06:09.633 --> 06:11.367
- I want to take Matt home
with me,

06:11.367 --> 06:14.166
'cause I think
he's very talented.

06:14.166 --> 06:16.400
- I'm gonna see
if I can juggle something.

06:16.400 --> 06:18.567
I don't know if I can do this.

06:18.567 --> 06:19.700
[laughs]

06:21.667 --> 06:23.200
- How are you?

06:23.200 --> 06:25.000
- So we're gonna do dinner
tonight.

06:25.000 --> 06:26.300
- Yes, dinner will be
around 8:30.

06:26.300 --> 06:27.333
We'll eat down here
with Captain Lee.

06:27.333 --> 06:28.734
He's coming to dinner.

06:28.734 --> 06:30.700
- Is he gonna wear
his white uniform?

06:30.700 --> 06:32.200
Will you join us for dinner
tonight or tomorrow night?

06:32.200 --> 06:33.700
- I think I might be able
to do that.

06:33.700 --> 06:35.667
- You have to wear your white.
- Okay.

06:35.667 --> 06:37.533
- 'Cause it's a white party.

06:37.533 --> 06:39.533
- I have to go iron it,
actually, yes.

06:39.533 --> 06:41.266
It's gonna be
a lovely evening.

06:41.266 --> 06:45.066
[upbeat music]

06:45.066 --> 06:48.133
- You going in?
- Let's get wet.

06:48.133 --> 06:50.033
- I want to get on the Jet Ski.

06:50.033 --> 06:52.700
- Okay, ladies, slowly
accelerate away from the boat.

06:52.700 --> 06:54.600
[motor roaring]

06:57.200 --> 06:59.033
- Okay,
this is day two schedule.

06:59.033 --> 07:00.700
This is so complicated.

07:00.700 --> 07:02.100
Dinner with the captain.

07:02.100 --> 07:04.567
That's gonna be on main deck.

07:04.567 --> 07:06.233
- First I have the captain
coming into the galley.

07:06.233 --> 07:08.233
He's looking at me like a hawk.

07:08.233 --> 07:10.033
And now he's gonna go
have dinner with the guests.

07:10.033 --> 07:11.567
[laughs]
Sh--.

07:11.567 --> 07:14.100
Maybe I should just
pack my bags now.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.100
- Disco party.
- When?

07:16.100 --> 07:18.500
- Tonight.

07:18.500 --> 07:21.166
What?
Oh, the white and neon party?

07:21.166 --> 07:22.300
Yeah.

07:22.300 --> 07:23.734
- Nico, Nico.

07:23.734 --> 07:24.734
Want to come up
with the wheelhouse?

07:24.734 --> 07:26.266
- F---.

07:27.700 --> 07:29.300
Captain.

07:29.300 --> 07:31.166
- I just wanted
to check in with you,

07:31.166 --> 07:32.767
see if everything was fine.

07:32.767 --> 07:34.500
- Yeah, everything--
you know, it's going smooth.

07:34.500 --> 07:36.133
- How's everybody
getting on with Kyle?

07:36.133 --> 07:37.500
- Everyone's getting along
fine,

07:37.500 --> 07:38.667
and they're actually melding
pretty good.

07:38.667 --> 07:40.633
- Cool.
I'm glad to hear that.

07:40.633 --> 07:42.467
I think subconsciously,

07:42.467 --> 07:44.066
Nico picked up
a lot of pointers from EJ,

07:44.066 --> 07:45.400
and I think he has
more confidence

07:45.400 --> 07:47.200
in his own ability,

07:47.200 --> 07:49.000
and it's showing through
to the deck team.

07:49.000 --> 07:50.734
They're either gonna step up
and get it done,

07:50.734 --> 07:53.100
or he's gonna drop the hammer
on their ass.

07:53.100 --> 07:54.767
He won't have to come to me
to do it.

07:54.767 --> 07:56.633
- If you need me, you know how
to get ahold of me.

07:56.633 --> 07:59.133
- Yeah.

07:59.133 --> 08:01.600
If you need me,
don't call.

08:01.600 --> 08:03.600
- Yeah.
- [laughs]

08:03.600 --> 08:05.100
- Jen, Jen, Kate.

08:05.100 --> 08:06.400
It's 5:00 now.

08:06.400 --> 08:10.100
I will be back at 18:00.
- Okay.

08:10.100 --> 08:12.500
[knock at door]
- Come in.

08:12.500 --> 08:14.133
Thank you!

08:14.133 --> 08:15.667
I'm so happy.

08:15.667 --> 08:18.033
It's always nice to see
a familiar face on board

08:18.033 --> 08:19.367
and, like, have new energy.

08:19.367 --> 08:23.133
Shag, marry, kill:
Bruno, Matt, Nico.

08:23.133 --> 08:26.266
If nothing else,
Kyle has returned to this boat

08:26.266 --> 08:27.533
as a great distraction.

08:27.533 --> 08:29.500
- I'd kill Bruno...
- Me too.

08:29.500 --> 08:30.633
- 'Cause he's
better-looking than me.

08:30.633 --> 08:31.633
- Oh.

08:31.633 --> 08:33.166
- I'd marry Matt,

08:33.166 --> 08:34.300
'cause you'd always win
an argument.

08:34.300 --> 08:36.100
- There would be no arguments.

08:36.100 --> 08:37.700
There would hardly be
conversations.

08:37.700 --> 08:39.166
- And he can cook.

08:39.166 --> 08:40.667
And I'd bang Nico.
- Yeah.

08:40.667 --> 08:42.266
- Just to see
what the fuss is about.

08:42.266 --> 08:44.567
- Just keep your feet away
from my Doritos.

08:44.567 --> 08:46.133
- Were you drinking chardonnay?

08:46.133 --> 08:47.567
- I don't need a new glass.

08:47.567 --> 08:48.633
You want to just bring
the bottle?

08:48.633 --> 08:49.700
[laughter]

08:49.700 --> 08:51.233
- Yeah, absolutely.

08:52.633 --> 08:55.367
- [laughs]

08:55.367 --> 08:59.166
[upbeat music]

08:59.166 --> 09:01.000
- The guests
are just clearing

09:01.000 --> 09:02.433
off the bridge deck aft,

09:02.433 --> 09:03.734
so we're gonna lift
the Skis first.

09:03.734 --> 09:05.533
Line's ready.
- Okay, stand by.

09:05.533 --> 09:07.467
- All right, I'm coming up now.

09:07.467 --> 09:10.333
Pull it--pull it harder.
- Yeah, Bru.

09:10.333 --> 09:12.333
- It's good.
- Yeah, that's good.

09:12.333 --> 09:14.166
- Well done, everybody.

09:14.166 --> 09:15.667
- How's everything
on the inside today?

09:15.667 --> 09:17.433
Has it cooled down
a little bit?

09:17.433 --> 09:20.400
- Jen said that Kate was
in a bad mood this morning--

09:20.400 --> 09:22.266
like, freaked out
on her again.

09:22.266 --> 09:23.667
Now she's happy.

09:23.667 --> 09:25.433
- Just riding
the roller coaster.

09:25.433 --> 09:27.600
Nico seems so much more calm

09:27.600 --> 09:30.400
and less stressed
and stuff now.

09:30.400 --> 09:32.033
- Nico and I have plans

09:32.033 --> 09:33.333
to stay in St. Maarten
a couple days.

09:33.333 --> 09:35.200
He's been really stressed out,

09:35.200 --> 09:37.400
so I think it will be
a good way to decompress

09:37.400 --> 09:39.300
from this crazy season.

09:39.300 --> 09:41.300
- Maybe you're gonna have
a good effect on him, Bri.

09:41.300 --> 09:42.567
- Ha!

09:42.567 --> 09:43.633
Maybe.

09:43.633 --> 09:50.667
♪ ♪

09:52.767 --> 09:54.166
- Put all the placemats out.

09:54.166 --> 09:56.033
Let's put Captain Lee there.

09:56.033 --> 09:58.033
Let's just break a glowstick
and pour it all over.

09:58.033 --> 10:00.333
How cute.
That makes me so happy.

10:00.333 --> 10:02.033
I love it.

10:02.033 --> 10:03.100
- I love cucumber,
and it's good for you.

10:03.100 --> 10:05.567
♪ ♪

10:05.567 --> 10:07.100
- Hey, Matt.

10:07.100 --> 10:08.166
- Hey, how are ya?

10:08.166 --> 10:09.633
- Uh...

10:09.633 --> 10:11.700
- We need to put
the boiling pot of water on.

10:11.700 --> 10:13.633
The way I see dinner tonight
is very simple.

10:13.633 --> 10:15.567
Just don't mess it up.

10:15.567 --> 10:18.166
Mahi.

10:18.166 --> 10:19.700
I don't want to disappoint
the crew,

10:19.700 --> 10:21.734
and I don't want to disappoint
Captain Lee.

10:21.734 --> 10:23.333
And plus, like, I'm tired
of getting my ass kicked.

10:23.333 --> 10:25.200
I'm gonna shut him up.

10:25.200 --> 10:26.400
I got to prove to him
that I can do this.

10:26.400 --> 10:28.200
This meal has to go perfectly.

10:29.400 --> 10:31.667
Aah!
That f---ing burns.

10:31.667 --> 10:34.100
- It smells fishy.

10:34.100 --> 10:35.233
Ugh, I wouldn't eat that.

10:36.533 --> 10:39.467
- You don't eat fish.
- I don't eat fish.

10:39.467 --> 10:40.500
- F--- me.

10:44.033 --> 10:44.367
[light upbeat music]

10:46.767 --> 10:52.066
♪ ♪

10:52.066 --> 10:53.467
- Shelly, that dress
is so pretty.

10:53.467 --> 10:57.066
- I wore this for Captain Lee.
[laughs]

10:57.066 --> 10:58.533
- Thank you.

10:58.533 --> 10:59.767
- You ladies look stunning
this evening.

10:59.767 --> 11:01.600
- Well, you look stunning too.

11:04.667 --> 11:08.633
- Look at Captain Lee
in his white neon party outfit.

11:08.633 --> 11:10.000
- It's really nice.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.767
- Mary Anne dresses me well.

11:11.767 --> 11:13.100
Let's go bust a move.

11:13.100 --> 11:14.233
- Yeah.

11:14.233 --> 11:15.667
- Cheers, girls.

11:15.667 --> 11:18.033
Guys, I'm bummed
this is our last night.

11:18.033 --> 11:20.133
- Captain Lee!
- Am I white enough?

11:20.133 --> 11:22.000
- Look at you!
- Captain Lee.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.266
- You look so handsome.

11:25.166 --> 11:26.567
- All right.

11:26.567 --> 11:29.133
You all look so lovely
this evening.

11:29.133 --> 11:30.500
- His little outfit's so cute.

11:30.500 --> 11:32.000
- It's so cute.
- I know.

