what I'm gonna do next.

24:06.033 --> 24:08.633
It's time to start to assess
what I'm gonna do

24:08.633 --> 24:10.467
after the season.

24:10.467 --> 24:12.300
- Two dinners left.

24:12.300 --> 24:15.100
- Two half days
and a full day.

24:15.100 --> 24:17.667
That's it.
Back to reality.

24:17.667 --> 24:20.500
The real world.
- This is the real world.

24:20.500 --> 24:22.367
- Yeah?

24:22.367 --> 24:25.533
- When you're on charter,
sh-- should be getting done.

24:25.533 --> 24:27.767
This morning, they had f--- all
when they woke up.

24:27.767 --> 24:29.600
- Kyle just got here,

24:29.600 --> 24:31.266
so I don't know why he's got
all these opinions,

24:31.266 --> 24:33.000
especially about the interior.

24:33.000 --> 24:34.233
- That sh-- needs to change.

24:40.133 --> 24:40.467
- Do you ladies want

24:40.467 --> 24:41.000
- Do you ladies want
anything else to drink?

24:42.467 --> 24:43.633
You all doing good?

24:43.633 --> 24:45.100
Another mimosa?
Sure.

24:47.200 --> 24:50.367
- Okay, deck guys,
let's pick up the anchor.

24:50.367 --> 24:53.066
- You want me in your hold?
- F--- off.

24:53.066 --> 24:55.100
- [laughs]

24:55.100 --> 24:56.567
- Steward.

25:00.700 --> 25:03.400
- Anchor is home and secure.

25:03.400 --> 25:05.133
- Roger that.

25:06.100 --> 25:07.700
- Good job, Nico.

25:07.700 --> 25:09.600
[light upbeat music]

25:12.266 --> 25:15.033
- I f---ing hate tension.
I don't need this in my world.

25:15.033 --> 25:16.166
That wasn't even funny.

25:20.033 --> 25:21.533
- All right,
let's get in position

25:21.533 --> 25:23.033
and get this thing
to the dock.

25:23.033 --> 25:25.500
- Finally.
- Ready on the aft.

25:25.500 --> 25:26.667
- Ready on the bow.

25:26.667 --> 25:28.266
- Listen, if you're not packed,

25:28.266 --> 25:30.567
probably start getting packed.

25:30.567 --> 25:33.133
All right, so I'm just
sticking this in here.

25:33.133 --> 25:34.400
- Bow's clear of the break
wall.

25:34.400 --> 25:36.266
You're good to start swinging.

25:36.266 --> 25:38.000
- That wind's pushing us.

25:38.000 --> 25:39.400
- Hey, Kyle, did you test
those controls?

25:39.400 --> 25:41.333
'Cause sometimes
they don't work.

25:41.333 --> 25:44.433
- Yeah, they're all tested
and ready to rock and roll.

25:44.433 --> 25:47.433
- Chuck it.
- The bow line's on.

25:47.433 --> 25:49.433
- You ready?

25:52.700 --> 25:54.567
- Talk to us, Kyle.
Do we need to come forward?

25:54.567 --> 25:56.066
- Yeah, you're good.

25:56.066 --> 25:57.533
- Lock that spring line.

25:57.533 --> 25:59.700
Lock the spring line.

25:59.700 --> 26:01.200
- I'm all good
on the stern, Captain.

26:01.200 --> 26:02.600
- Hey, Bruno, tighten that.

26:02.600 --> 26:04.266
Tighten that.
This one.

26:04.266 --> 26:06.700
Lock it down.
- Well done, everybody.

26:06.700 --> 26:09.600
Outstanding.
- Nice driving, Cap.

26:09.600 --> 26:11.700
This whole season has been
a big learning experience

26:11.700 --> 26:13.700
not just for the deck crew
but also for me.

26:13.700 --> 26:15.400
Even though
I may not be boatswain,

26:15.400 --> 26:17.333
I do take my job seriously.

26:17.333 --> 26:19.300
- We're all good.
Thank you, guys.

26:19.300 --> 26:21.633
- Slow, slow, slow, slow,
slow, slow.

26:21.633 --> 26:23.100
It's a big angle.

26:23.100 --> 26:24.467
- All crew, all crew,

26:24.467 --> 26:25.600
I need everybody
on the aft deck

26:25.600 --> 26:27.200
ASAP.

26:27.200 --> 26:28.600
- Let's hurry up.
They're getting off.

26:28.600 --> 26:30.333
- Jesus Christ,
always on my back,

26:30.333 --> 26:32.633
riding me so hard
this season, Kelley.

26:32.633 --> 26:35.300
- Oh, f--- you.
- [laughs]

26:43.233 --> 26:44.700
- Oh, here they come.
Here they come.

26:46.767 --> 26:48.467
- Bye.
- Thank you...

26:48.467 --> 26:49.600
- Thank you for everything.
- So much.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.200
- I hope you enjoyed it.

26:51.200 --> 26:53.233
- We had a wonderful time.

26:53.233 --> 26:56.100
- Thank you.
Enjoy your trip home.

26:56.100 --> 26:59.100
- Thank you so much.
- Aw!

26:59.100 --> 27:01.467
- Shelly.
- Thank you.

27:01.467 --> 27:03.233
Y'all were so lovely.

27:03.233 --> 27:05.100
- And on behalf of all of us,
Captain Lee,

27:05.100 --> 27:07.633
your guys are just amazing.

27:07.633 --> 27:09.133
Five star, five star.

27:09.133 --> 27:10.633
I can't say it
even any more than that.

27:10.633 --> 27:12.266
It was perfect.

27:12.266 --> 27:14.233
The food, Matt--
I mean, you're so talented.

27:14.233 --> 27:15.533
- Thank you.

27:15.533 --> 27:17.133
- Your salad dressing's
off the chart.

27:17.133 --> 27:19.000
- Thank you.

27:19.000 --> 27:20.266
I knew the guests
would love my cooking.

27:20.266 --> 27:21.333
Captain was dead wrong
about me.

27:21.333 --> 27:22.767
In your face!

27:22.767 --> 27:24.400
- This is yours.
Thank you so much.

27:24.400 --> 27:26.133
You guys were just amazing.

27:26.133 --> 27:27.667
Bon voyage.
- Bye.

27:27.667 --> 27:30.100
all: Bye!
- Take care.

27:30.100 --> 27:32.233
- Okay, let's go to work.
- Thank you.

27:32.233 --> 27:35.266
[upbeat music]

27:35.266 --> 27:38.266
♪ ♪

27:38.266 --> 27:40.133
- Hey, what do you think
about the tip?

27:40.133 --> 27:41.400
- I think it'll be good.

27:41.400 --> 27:43.400
- I think I'm excited.

27:43.400 --> 27:46.300
I think maybe we would have got
$2,000 each, hopefully.

27:46.300 --> 27:48.266
- I need everybody
in the crew mess

27:48.266 --> 27:50.133
in five minutes.

27:50.133 --> 27:51.166
- Copy that.

27:51.166 --> 27:53.734
- Show me some tip money.

27:58.500 --> 28:00.300
- [sighs]

28:00.300 --> 28:02.300
All in all, I think
it was a good charter.

28:02.300 --> 28:04.700
Your girls did a good job
on service.

28:04.700 --> 28:07.000
The toy situation
came off well.

28:07.000 --> 28:08.667
You guys did a good job
with that.

28:08.667 --> 28:12.266
That being said,
let's get right to the tip.

28:14.266 --> 28:16.266
15,000.

28:17.400 --> 28:20.300
Yeah, Bruno, that's exactly
the look I got.

28:20.300 --> 28:23.300
It's like we're just
f---ing stuck on 15,000.

28:23.300 --> 28:25.300
I'm not impressed.

28:25.300 --> 28:26.734
That's mediocre.

28:26.734 --> 28:30.567
If you have one mediocre player
on a team,

28:30.567 --> 28:33.066
you have a mediocre team.

28:33.066 --> 28:36.033
I've been wanting to see
that $2,500 tip,

28:36.033 --> 28:37.600
and it's not happening.

28:37.600 --> 28:40.066
We've got one charter left,

28:40.066 --> 28:42.433
so what I want out of you guys

28:42.433 --> 28:46.033
is to collectively
sit down here,

28:46.033 --> 28:49.033
hash this sh-- out
in a constructive way,

28:49.033 --> 28:51.300
and figure out
what we're doing wrong.

28:51.300 --> 28:54.734
The important thing is that
we nail this next charter.

28:54.734 --> 28:56.567
I'm almost at my wits' end
here,

28:56.567 --> 28:57.734
because it seems like

28:57.734 --> 29:00.066
we get one situation solved,

29:00.066 --> 29:01.533
like with the deck crew.

29:01.533 --> 29:03.567
Now they're functioning
as a team.

29:03.567 --> 29:05.467
But then I've got the chef
that's just playing it safe.

29:05.467 --> 29:08.333
And so now I'm hoping
we can finish strong,

29:08.333 --> 29:10.633
but that's all it is;
it's a distant hope.

29:10.633 --> 29:12.767
Okay?

29:12.767 --> 29:15.333
- Lash it out
in the crew mess.

29:15.333 --> 29:16.700
- I'm actually very impressed

29:16.700 --> 29:19.500
with Captain Lee's
observations.

29:19.500 --> 29:21.367
People think he doesn't know
what goes on

29:21.367 --> 29:24.100
below the wheelhouse,
but he does,

29:24.100 --> 29:27.200
and his tip meeting speech
proves it.

29:27.200 --> 29:28.767
I think the deck crew
is stepping up.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.600
There haven't been
any major complaints

29:30.600 --> 29:32.233
with the interior.

29:32.233 --> 29:34.100
I think it's mostly aimed
at Matt.

29:34.100 --> 29:35.767
The galley is suffering.

29:35.767 --> 29:37.367
Okay, I'll go first.

29:37.367 --> 29:38.633
What would y'all like
to see differently

29:38.633 --> 29:40.333
from the interior?

29:42.700 --> 29:45.467
- When you're on charter,
sh-- should be getting done.

29:45.467 --> 29:47.166
Captain was talking about

29:47.166 --> 29:48.767
how we're gonna make
more f---ing money.

29:48.767 --> 29:50.400
What sets the tone
for the beginning of the day?

29:50.400 --> 29:52.266
Service as soon as
they wake up.

29:52.266 --> 29:53.767
This morning, they had f--- all
when they woke up.

29:53.767 --> 29:56.000
They had nothing.

29:56.000 --> 29:57.667
- Kyle just got here,

29:57.667 --> 29:59.133
so I don't know why he's got
all these opinions,

29:59.133 --> 30:01.100
especially about the interior.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.000
And he can't be
this uncomfortably

30:03.000 --> 30:04.633
too close of a friend

30:04.633 --> 30:06.633
but then also come in
with opinions

30:06.633 --> 30:08.000
about how I'm running the boat.

30:08.000 --> 30:10.600
- That sh-- needs to change.

30:10.600 --> 30:13.133
Where the f--- do you get off
calling someone a whore?

30:13.133 --> 30:14.600
- I don't need this sh--!

30:14.600 --> 30:15.633
- Whoa, whoa.
[all talking at once]

30:19.700 --> 30:20.233
- What sets the tone

30:20.233 --> 30:20.667
- What sets the tone
for the beginning of the day?

30:22.667 --> 30:24.533
Service as soon as
they wake up.

30:24.533 --> 30:25.767
This morning, they had f--- all
when they woke up.

30:25.767 --> 30:27.266
- That was the only time.

30:27.266 --> 30:28.633
- 'Cause the chef's
cooking breakfast.

30:28.633 --> 30:30.233
- You know, I trust Kyle,

30:30.233 --> 30:33.300
but instead he decides
to run his mouth

30:33.300 --> 30:35.300
to the person
that I least want him

30:35.300 --> 30:37.033
to run his mouth to.

30:37.033 --> 30:39.233
- I will take over
the early service this charter,

30:39.233 --> 30:41.300
because I've done
many breakfast services.

30:41.300 --> 30:43.767
And what else?

30:43.767 --> 30:47.233
- Matt, I think you did
a great job this charter.

30:47.233 --> 30:49.667
- Maybe take as much risk
as possible.

30:49.667 --> 30:51.300
- Risk.
- Go extreme.

30:51.300 --> 30:52.700
Like, as much, like--

30:52.700 --> 30:54.133
- I have a feeling
the next guests

30:54.133 --> 30:56.266
are gonna want something crazy.

30:56.266 --> 30:58.133
I have something up my sleeve.

30:58.133 --> 30:59.700
- To really end this charter
season on a high note,

30:59.700 --> 31:01.700
it's important
that Matt delivers

31:01.700 --> 31:03.700
his best charter food ever.

31:03.700 --> 31:05.433
We have guests arriving
in 21 hours.

31:05.433 --> 31:06.567
- Vama-vama-vamos.

31:06.567 --> 31:08.333
Good talk, good talk.

31:14.166 --> 31:15.600
- Hey, Ma, how's it going?

31:15.600 --> 31:17.734
You all right?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

31:17.734 --> 31:19.700
- You don't sound all right.
- I've been struggling a lot.

31:19.700 --> 31:22.533
- Everybody's struggling, Ma.
It's not easy.

31:22.533 --> 31:24.166
- I know that.

31:24.166 --> 31:26.333
- Nothing.
Working, working, working.

31:26.333 --> 31:29.467
My family situation right now
is on rocky terms.

31:29.467 --> 31:31.300
Dealing with losing
your best friend

31:31.300 --> 31:32.734
and your little brother,

31:32.734 --> 31:35.066
it's kind of just changed
my perspective

31:35.066 --> 31:37.066
that all the bullsh--
doesn't matter.

31:37.066 --> 31:38.600
Family, that's all
that matters.

31:38.600 --> 31:40.667
All right, well, I got
to get back to work.

31:40.667 --> 31:42.166
I just thought I'd call you.

31:42.166 --> 31:43.700
All right?
I love you.

31:43.700 --> 31:45.433
- I love you.
- Thanks, Ma.

31:45.433 --> 31:47.400
All right, bye.

31:47.400 --> 31:49.367
[sighs]
F---, f---.

31:52.033 --> 31:54.533
- So, Jen, what do you think
Kyle was talking about

31:54.533 --> 31:56.367
when it comes to the breakfast?

31:56.367 --> 31:59.200
- There was dirty silverware
still in the dishwasher.

31:59.200 --> 32:01.066
I had to rerun it.

32:01.066 --> 32:03.367
I had to hand-wash it
even after the second time.

32:03.367 --> 32:05.100
- As soon as I asked Jen
about breakfast,

32:05.100 --> 32:07.200
I know that she slept in
and is lying to me,

32:07.200 --> 32:09.600
because she gets defensive.

32:09.600 --> 32:12.066
- Why am I ironing
Chris's shirt?

32:25.767 --> 32:28.033
- [sighs]

32:28.033 --> 32:30.033
- Matt, Kate, Nico,
I need you guys

32:30.033 --> 32:32.066
in the crew mess
for a preference sheet meeting.

32:32.066 --> 32:33.500
- Copy.
- Copy.

32:33.500 --> 32:35.100
- Here we go, baby.

32:35.100 --> 32:36.600
Charter nine.

32:39.100 --> 32:40.133
- Howdy, howdy.

32:40.133 --> 32:41.400
- Hey.
- Hi.

32:41.400 --> 32:44.633
- So how did
your little powwow go?

32:44.633 --> 32:46.467
- I think it was productive.

32:46.467 --> 32:48.000
- Yeah?
-Yeah.

32:48.000 --> 32:49.266
- Last charter.
I guess we'll find out.

32:49.266 --> 32:50.500
- Mm-hmm.

32:50.500 --> 32:52.500
- Six people, I think.

32:52.500 --> 32:54.533
- Timothy.

32:54.533 --> 32:56.500
- We had him on "Ohana."

32:56.500 --> 32:58.100
He's a character.

32:58.100 --> 32:59.467
- I planned to give you guys
22 grand,

32:59.467 --> 33:00.500
but there were
some things wrong,

33:00.500 --> 33:02.500
so we'll rip it.

33:02.500 --> 33:04.133
- Okay.
- So 17.

33:04.133 --> 33:05.533
- He's a financial person.

33:05.533 --> 33:07.400
He's like,
"That's gonna cost ya."

33:07.400 --> 33:09.100
- So stoked.

33:09.100 --> 33:10.400
- This guy sounds like
a douchebag.

33:10.400 --> 33:12.000
- He's a repeat charter client

33:12.000 --> 33:13.667
celebrating
ten-year anniversary

33:13.667 --> 33:15.633
of his teaching company.

33:15.633 --> 33:18.500
Timothy is bringing
his top three employees

33:18.500 --> 33:20.700
as a thank-you
for their dedication.

33:20.700 --> 33:23.033
- That's nice.
- He wants to go all out.

33:23.033 --> 33:24.700
The more extravagant,
the better.

33:24.700 --> 33:26.300
- Oh, got to bring it.

33:26.300 --> 33:28.567
- We're gonna do
some fireworks on a beach.

33:28.567 --> 33:31.400
And got a chef's choice
tasting meal.

33:31.400 --> 33:33.400
- I see that.
- Any questions?

33:33.400 --> 33:35.400
- Can we please him?
Is he happy?

33:35.400 --> 33:36.700
Was he complaining
all the time?

33:36.700 --> 33:38.300
- He is particular,

33:38.300 --> 33:40.133
but he will let you know
what he wants.

33:40.133 --> 33:41.400
- Did you get my list
of ingredients?

33:41.400 --> 33:43.433
Did you find sea cucumber
ovaries?

33:43.433 --> 33:44.533
- That's the one thing
I didn't--

33:44.533 --> 33:46.033
- Oh!

33:46.033 --> 33:48.166
- We had this conversation
with him.

33:48.166 --> 33:49.700
He doesn't follow instructions.

33:49.700 --> 33:51.400
Ay ay ay.

33:51.400 --> 33:53.700
- As long as you just deliver
what he asks for,

33:53.700 --> 33:55.433
he is happy.
- Okay.

33:55.433 --> 33:57.266
- Part of me
doesn't really want

33:57.266 --> 34:00.300
to warn Matt about
how demanding Timothy Sykes is

34:00.300 --> 34:02.033
when it comes to food,

34:02.033 --> 34:03.200
'cause I think it'll just
freak him out even more.

34:03.200 --> 34:05.000
And let's face it.

34:05.000 --> 34:06.333
He's probably not gonna nail it
either way.

34:06.333 --> 34:08.066
- We've got, like, 18 hours
to get ready.

34:08.066 --> 34:10.433
So whatever it takes,
you need to get it done.

34:18.567 --> 34:20.066
- I would like to get out
of uniform

34:20.066 --> 34:21.467
and get off the boat.

34:21.467 --> 34:23.200
But I think that if we went
the entire crew,

34:23.200 --> 34:26.066
it would just be chitchat
and a waste of time.

34:26.066 --> 34:27.667
Let's change, just go
to a nearby restaurant,

34:27.667 --> 34:30.000
and we can talk
and make our orders together

34:30.000 --> 34:31.200
and talk about this charter.

34:31.200 --> 34:32.600
- Okay.

34:32.600 --> 34:33.734
- We don't have a choice
at this point.

34:33.734 --> 34:35.467
I've seen what Matt can do.

34:35.467 --> 34:37.433
Timothy Sykes
is coming on board.

34:37.433 --> 34:39.200
I think it's time
that I just take the wheels

34:39.200 --> 34:41.200
and drive this charter home
to Good Food Town.

34:41.200 --> 34:43.600
So it's like a work dinner.

34:48.767 --> 34:50.567
- The night is young.

34:50.567 --> 34:52.433
I'm feeling frisky.

34:52.433 --> 34:54.233
I'm having a great hair day.

34:54.233 --> 34:55.767
I think the girls
will come out to play,

34:55.767 --> 34:58.066
and we'll see what happens.

34:58.066 --> 34:59.500
- Don't wait up.

34:59.500 --> 35:01.100
- All right, guys, let's go.

35:01.100 --> 35:02.367
- I think you're overdressed,
Kyle.

35:02.367 --> 35:04.367
- [laughs]

35:05.734 --> 35:07.567
- This is a great idea.

35:07.567 --> 35:09.767
- I didn't want to not get
prepared for the charter,

35:09.767 --> 35:11.433
but I also really wanted
to leave the boat.

35:11.433 --> 35:13.066
- Right.

35:13.066 --> 35:14.233
- I feel like we're going
to a study group.

35:14.233 --> 35:15.600
We're gonna go
do our homework.

35:15.600 --> 35:16.633
- All right, let's do this.

35:16.633 --> 35:17.633
I like it that I'm on top.

35:17.633 --> 35:19.233
- [laughs]

35:19.233 --> 35:21.500
- Ah, my sunburn!
F--- off, f---ing bitch.

35:21.500 --> 35:23.233
- Okay?
- It works for me.

35:23.233 --> 35:24.500
- Yeah, I like it.

35:24.500 --> 35:26.367
This guy just looks
intimidating.

35:26.367 --> 35:27.467
- He is, and he isn't.

35:27.467 --> 35:29.133
I think he grew up

35:29.133 --> 35:30.734
watching "Lifestyles
of the Rich and Famous"

35:30.734 --> 35:33.367
and he wants champagne wishes,
caviar dreams.

35:33.367 --> 35:34.667
- Ugh.
- Cheers.

35:34.667 --> 35:36.233
- Cheers. Thanks, Kate.
- Uh-huh.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.000
- Here we are. All right.

35:42.233 --> 35:45.333
- Hey, I'm curious
what everyone's getting into

35:45.333 --> 35:46.734
after we're done.

35:46.734 --> 35:48.400
I mean, I know
what we're getting into.

35:48.400 --> 35:50.233
- A bed?
- Huh?

35:50.233 --> 35:52.667
- I'm gonna go back to Portugal
to get my visa.

35:52.667 --> 35:55.633
I want to go to LA, California,
all those places.

35:55.633 --> 35:57.266
- What about everyone else?

35:57.266 --> 35:59.000
Where you going?

35:59.000 --> 36:02.633
- I'm going back to Charleston
for probably--

36:02.633 --> 36:04.400
- Yeah, yup.

36:04.400 --> 36:06.367
- This is the first restaurant
I've seen this thingy.

36:06.367 --> 36:08.133
- It's like the deep fryer.
- Yeah, it's really funny.

36:08.133 --> 36:10.433
It's homemade potatoes,
so it's really good.

